node.text:

#STAYLOVE
・
5 年前 の Zepp Tokyo 
君と出逢うまでは  音楽に身を委ね 
自由に生きる僕には 「結婚」なんて
ほど遠いと思っていた
・
だけど  音楽を本気で楽しむ
無邪気に笑う 君の横顔に
今思えば あの瞬間から
惹かれていたかもしれない
・
名古屋⇆東京の遠距離
どんなに離れていても  君は
僕の世界を明るくしてくれた
・
どんなに辛いことがあったとしても
君となら乗り越えていける そう思えたのは
周りの人を幸せにできる
君の人柄がそうしてくれたんだ
・
今までもこれからもありがとう
・
ここに集う大切な友人たちの前で
感謝と永遠の愛を伝えたい
・
そして、いつの日か
この広い世界で生きていこう
・
Our dream is to live in USA
and have a big house with a big dog.
 I promise that your dreams come true...
・
・

Trying to stay positive. Because at the end of the day, I’m still standing here with all of my privileges. I am a healthy able body person. I didn’t lose my job during the pandemic. I am supported by my family and friends. I have an abundance of blessings. So while I am anxious about what my job will look like for the 2020-2021 school year (Im a school psychologist for those who didn’t know), I know that I have skills and talents that will be needed to support my team.  While my safety and health are priorities , so is keeping a perspective. Thanks for attending my TedTalk.

node.text:
On Tuesday August 18, 2020, the Guam Police Department (GPD) was made aware of two police officers who had tested positive for COVID-19 and are currently in home isolation.  The two officers are assigned to GPD’s specialized units, which have minimal contact to the greater community. 

 GPD is working alongside the DPHSS with ongoing contact tracing with GPD personnel who may have been exposed to the two officers. 
In line with GPD’s COVID-19 Operations and to help mitigate the spread of COVID-19, should any member of the community wishing to file a complaint with any of our four respective precincts, are asked to call the precincts and wait in their car for further instructions from our officers. The following are the telephone numbers to the respective precincts: 

 Dededo Precinct Command: 632-9808/11

Tumon-Tamuning Precinct Command: 649-6330

Central Precinct Command: 475-8541

Southern Precinct Command: 472-8915

Police Dispatch: 472-8911/8615/7

 In light of the island moving into PCOR1, the Guam Police Department remains committed in providing safety and security to the greater community and will continue to respond to calls or any emergency needs.

この広い世界で生きていこう

and have a big house with a big dog.
 I promise that your dreams come true...

node.text:
“Japanese Zoo Employs Capybara”
Izu Shaboten Zoo, also known as the Cactus Park, is located in Shizuoka prefecture, famous for being the home of Mt. Fuji. The zoo is the very first in Japan to showcase capybaras soaking in hot springs. 

They also have an animal restaurant with life-sized capybara and red panda plushies. The restaurant has rearranged their layout to maintain social distancing, following proper COVID-19 guidelines. 

Capybaras and red pandas plushies also share tables with you not only for social distancing but also to accompany you during your meal. You don’t have to feel alone during your meal trying to maintain social distancing anymore!

(Don’t worry, they are regularly sanitized!)

📸Credit: @capyqru

Georgia & Lena: “The aims of our designs are to change people’s perspectives and behaviours to protect those who are vulnerable, specifically the elderly, even if in an indirect manner. We looked at principles such as visibility, exposure effect, proximity, framing, picture superiority effect, storytelling, empathy and more. Our concept combines graphical and tangible methods to simulate the presence of vulnerable bodies in widely frequented public spaces such as supermarkets and buses.”

node.text:
✅ El virus utiliza un receptor celular ECA2 para ingresar a la célula e infectarla. Estos receptores están en pulmón, endotelio, corazón, intestino y riñón.
.
‼ Se comentaba que aquellos pacientes de riesgo que eran hipertensos y diabéticos, medicados con IECA o ARAII ( enalapril, valsartan, losartan), tenían susceptibilidad aumentada de infectarse; dado que tenían el sistema  ECA2 sobre expresado. Con lo cual generó alteración en los medios y los pacientes suspendían su medicación para no correr riesgos.
.
✅ Recientemente se público un artículo en el New England Journal del 1/5/2020, donde evaluó si existía una relación entre los pacientes bajo tratamiento con IECA o ARAII y el riesgo de covid-19. 
.
‼ Los IECA y ARAII NO TUVIERON ASOCIACION CON EL COVID-19. Lo que si se vio, es que los pacientes infectados eran más añosos, tenían hipertensión, enfermedad coronaria, insuficiencia cardiaca y renal.
.
💊‼ Claramente estos datos poblacionales nos dan tranquilidad para el uso de IECA y ARAII en estos pacientes. Las sociedades científicas del mundo, AVALARON EL USO DE ESTOS FÁRMACOS. Una vez más los datos son más contundentes que las hipótesis.

🩺Fuente: Sociedad Argentina de Cardiología, Consejo de hipertensión.

The Virgin Money Unity Arena is a new pop-up venue in England that is dedicated to providing a safe concert-going experience during COVID-19 times. Social distancing will continue to be enforced upon guests’ arrival, the company said. Cars will be parked with a 2 meter distance from each other, and the concert attendees will be guided to their personal viewing areas — also distanced 2 meters apart by staff.

In order for us to ensure the safety of our patients and practitioners please take note of the following when visiting @dunkeldmedicalanddentalcentre 

The security personnel at the front gate will take temperatures of all visitors.

No mask no entry.

Please sanitize your hands when entering the centre and fill out the necessary forms. 

Only the person consulting will be allowed in the centre with the exception of a minor accompanied by a parent. 

Please adhere to social distancing at all times. It is advisable to wait in your car until you are called in for your appointment to avoid patients crowding the waiting area. 

If you are symptomatic or have been in contact with a positive case please call in for a telephonic consult, we will then send you an electronic request form for testing. ⁣

node.text:
Came across an article by @joshua_becker and it was full of gems! What we consume matters ✨ 

Here is an extract from the article...

 ‘What we consume always determines the lives that we live.

We can see this, most easily, with the food that we eat.

But this is a principle with further reaching application than the food we eat. This is a truth that rings true with almost everything we choose to consume: books, music, television, websites, just to name a few.

Think about it. If you choose to read books and listen to podcasts primarily about business and productivity, your mind is going to sharpen its focus on those things. You will begin to see the world in this way and act accordingly.’

Consume with caution and when it comes to food choose *whispers* ‘The Farmer’s Hamper’ ✨

•OREGON DAY 2•

Afternoon on Day 2 consisted of making my bouquet + curling my hair + putting on my hot girl disguise courtesy of @kellystrackofficial bridal makeup on YouTube + wedding day playlist. 

I decided to DIY most of my elopement day because
 1) I’m cheap 
2) I didn’t want to have a lot of time on my hands for nerves
3) I wanted it to feel as elopement-y as possible, if that makes any sense

Because we were supposed to be married in Ireland, a lot of my wedding plans involved incorporating Irish traditions into our day.  So having wildflowers & a more natural look was important to me when picking flowers and putting it together.  I even tried to convince @jsears90 to let me snip a few flowers on our walk but he didn’t go for it.  I got ~5 different bouquets from Trader Joe’s in Portland to start with and then I pulled them apart and paired flowers together.  So for every yellow I did a white and then I filled in the purple and red and finished it off with 3 eucalyptus evenly spaced.  Wrapping it with the floral tape and then the ribbon took 2 pairs of hands, but overall I was pleasantly surprised by how quick & easy it was to make my #bouquet 
PRO TIP: Don’t use your fancy Kate Spade scissors to cut flower stems 🤣🤦🏻‍♀️

And for any #brides, feel free to use my Elopement playlist. 

https://open.spotify.com/playlist/1TvsahKNRWuWdloxdd3qsH?si=5rHB1a3aQhOrmFwlw0-2qg

Repost from our guest @josievmai - Uhm... how’s it already mid August? I’m not complaining though, since that means Fall is coming 😆 ⠀
—⠀
This photo was taken this past weekend at @rivermountain #rivermountain - our first #getaway since Covid started 😱 the boo and I have been craving a vacation or change of scenery - but it’s been difficult to 1) find the time from our busy work schedule, and 2) find a place that wasn’t packed with people. This was the best of both - a quick 2 hour drive from DC, out in the grand outdoors with SO MUCH space and nature to breathe fresh air, they follow all Covid precautions and cleanliness, and they have internet service 👌 We plan to go back sometime to have a full #remote #wfh week there, while still being able to relax and unwind, have a bonfire with s’mores, do hikes and walks, #socialdistance yoga classes, go to bed with starry night skies and wake up to the beautiful daylight. It was a perfect weekend away from the hustle and bustle and the River Mountain crew were SO kind and accommodating. I’ve been recommending this new lodging experience to all my local friends in the PA/DC/MD/VA areas 👌 they open officially September 4! Go check them out at @rivermountain rivermountain.org to learn more and book your stay!

node.text:
We love doing our wellness clinics for the public.  They are for ANYONE in need with their pets.  Our main focus is basic medical care such as core vaccines for puppies, kittens and adult dogs and cats, de-worming, flea treatment, micro-chipping, nail trims, heart worm tests, Felv/fiv testing and anything else that we are able to take care of within our means.

UNFORTUNATELY - we have been seeing at the past few clinics many pets that were just adopted/bought and many  of these newly adopted/bought animals have been sick. Kittens have been coming in sick, not being fixed, vaccinated or micro-chipped and a severely sick puppies.

Please know that at the very least you should be getting a puppy or kitten who is spayed/neutered, who has age appropriate vaccinated,  they should also be de-wormed and flea treated. and its healthy, no coughing, sneezing, gooey eyes or nose.

We have taken on the cost for these clients to pay for their pets to get medically healthy and do what was needed for the pets, that the people who didn't do it but should have.  This is why you need to research where you get your new fur-member from. 

Please donate so that we can continue to help the public and their pets during their time of need.  We run a free food pantry daily for anyone in need.  Our Wellness clinic is run on donations as well and that is how we were able to take on the added medical for our clients pets

Below is the agricultural code/law in which it shows what the public is suppose to get with the adoption fee or purchase price.

.
.
.
.

“As much as we believe we have worked diligently to help create a healthy and safe campus living and learning environment, we believe the current data presents an untenable situation.” Read more at washingtonpost.com  #Repost @washingtonpost
• • • • • •
The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, one of the largest schools in the country to bring students to campus for in-person teaching, said Monday it will pivot to all-remote instruction for undergraduates after testing showed a pattern of rapid spread of the novel coronavirus.

node.text:
Lesson “Plants.” 🌵🖌
•
To all the educators out there that have and have not yet returned to in-person classes (including my mama and close friends), I feel you. 💕 As an “essential worker” myself, I am right there with you when it comes to the ultimate question that weighs on our minds.
•
“How can I safely return to work amidst CoVid-19 while protecting the health of myself and my family?”
•
There is no perfect answer. There is no happy solution. It is the unfortunate truth of having to decide how comfortable we are to return to work or not at all.
•
All I can say is, control your own actions. Don’t give in to the negativity of the situation at hand - all the pricks and shadiness of others. Focus on you and how best to protect yourself and your loved ones.
•
You got this, friend. 🤙🏽
•

node.text:
Whilst i've been more prolific in posting lately I want to acknoweldge the reality of our present situation as I am not taking the privilege of being able to visit the wall lightly - remember a month ago, by law, I wasn't allowed to be here!

Whilst lockdown is being lifted, Covid-19 is still here - as much as we wish it weren't.

I am still washing my hands far more than my skin would like, because C-19 hasn't disappeared. 

I am still observing physical distancing, because C-19 hasn't disappeared. 

I am still wearing a mask in public to protect others, because C-19 hasn't disappeared. 

When i'm not wearing a mask (as above) it's because I am placing the onus on myself to get out to the wall first thing in the morning when no-one else is around, because i still need to climb for my pysical and mental health, oh, and because C-19 hasn't disappeared!

Wash your hands.
Keep your distance.
Wear a mask.

They are pretty minor sacrifices in the grand scheme of things and we're going to have to 'get through this' one way or another, how about we get to the other side able to say we all did so with care, empathy, and compassion? 

Just a thought.

node.text:
Focus op wat u wel kunt beïnvloeden
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Er blijven in deze tijd veel zaken bestaan waar u geen invloed op heeft. Daar kunt u veel tijd aan kwijt zijn, maar dit verandert niets aan de situatie. Het is zinvoller om te focussen op de zaken waar u wel invloed op heeft, bijvoorbeeld uw gedrag. Er bestaan geen garanties, maar met een zorgvuldige afweging tussen veiligheid en vrijheid, waarbij u rekening houdt met uzelf, uw omgeving en de maatschappij, kunnen we de gevolgen van het coronavirus zo goed mogelijk beperken. Voor een goede risico-inschatting is informatie nodig. We weten nog lang niet alles van het coronavirus, het grijze gebied. Dit moet bespreekbaar blijven.

De volgende tien posts zullen vragen bespreken die ik tegenkom in de huisartsenpraktijk en ook in het dagelijks leven. Ik hoop u hiermee meer informatie te geven, waardoor u beter uw eigen risico-inschatting kan maken.

node.text:
#luxelakesa4artmuseum#60daysoflockdown
Day 56 Home: The Integrality of the Self

Artist: 姚纯纯 (Yao Chunchun) & Gabriel Moraes Aquino @yao_chunchun @gabri.moraes
Location: Hangzhou, China; Paris, France
Type: Video
Full video address: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9JGzeeis-D8 

How do we define “home?” Is home just a space? Or is it an energy? Is home just the shelter of a roof and walls? Or is it just an emotional connection, referring to a place or a person? I believe that home comes from the integrality of our own bodies in which symbiosis and confrontation, linkage and restraint, protection and control all exist.
